The paper presents a deep learning approach for early detection of sepsis using electronic health record data. This involves the use of machine learning models and data analysis, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the study involves the use of healthcare data and focuses on improving patient outcomes, which aligns with the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction and Medical Systems).
